VPaniniyavyakaranodharanakosah &#151;  The Paninian grammar through its examples. Vol. 1 &#151;  Udhaharanasamaraharah &#151;  The book of examples: 40,000 entries for a text.F. Grimal, V. Vemnataraja Sarma, V. Srivatsankacharya, S. Lakshminarasimham, IFPIEFEO  -   Rashtriya Sanskrit Vidyapeetha Tirupati, 2005, (CD-ROM), Language &#151;  Sanskrit, English, Rs. 300.The dictionary of examples of Panini's grammar is intended to facilitate access to the fundamental treatise on Sanskrit grammar.The first volume, entitled, `The Book of Examples' is intended to give a simple and clear overview of the basic data embodied in all the examples. This CD-ROM permits one, first to locate the references to a given example, and secondly, to know which examples are attached to a given ruleBhairava Sahasrapratimavalih &#151;  Iconographie de la forme terrible de Siva en Inde du Sud I &#151;  Iconography of the terrible form of Siva in South India.Edition par K. Ladrech, avec la collaboration de N. Dejenne, K. Ramesh Kumar, IFPIEFEO, 2005, (CD_ROM), Language: French, English, Rs. 300.This bilingual French/English database assembles one thousand images of Bhairava (principally sculptures) in Tamil Nadu, Karnataka and Andhra Pradesh, thereby presenting a vast panorama of representations of the deity in South India.The photographic documentation, derived mainly from the photographic collection of the French Institute of Pondicherry, is accompanied by descriptive fiches. A search-engine enables the user to bring together all the various data and to select images based on specific search criteria. Keywords: database, iconography, sculpture, South India, Siva-Bhairava.Bottom Template Starts
